cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the problem of ranking brands in an e-commerce website. It also involves feature engineering and machine learning models, which are commonly used in IR research. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes modifications to the Attention-GRU model to improve its performance. 

The Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as feature engineering and text classification. 

The Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category is less likely but still possible as e-commerce websites are often targeted by cyber attacks and the proposed ranking system may have implications for security. 

The Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with user behavior in e-commerce websites and the impact of brand on user decision-making.
